choices.text:
hitchhiking a ride in a pick-up. Sometimes we do it and sometimes we don’t and this morning we decided to try it!!

So one of the crew says he knows someone who lives close to the grocery store that we could hitch a ride with. We go for a nice walk and manage to catch him walking out of his yard, with his wife and sister-in-law. We ask him if he is heading that direction and he is nice enough to say yes.

So we hop in the car and head out, leaving the girls to walk back home and meet us later.

The guys ask us are we going to eat jalalo and chili pikliz today? Never heard of that dish, it is also called pates which is french I think…lol

We have never heard of these Island treats actually…lol

They tell us that it is made with intestines of goat plus goat brain! I had to share this picture with you to embarrass “Bro, Elune” but he actually claims to like this dish.

Are you hungry now? How in the world do you eat something like that?

How about fried frog legs?

Just to get my excited…lol

To get my attention, they stopped to get some beef bones to roast. Good thing. It came in handy…lol

I managed to get a close up shot of the chicken…lol

I am not sure if they season the meat before they cook it??

And I am not even going to show you
